  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Technician",
  "description": "<p><u><strong>Mechanical Technician</strong></u></p>\n<p>-Responsible for installation, commissioning, repair and maintenance of port equipment (e.g., RTG, STS, Spreaders).</p>\n<p>-Inspect and replace mechanical components to ensure equipment reliability.</p>\n<p>-Assist in equipment handling, assembly and testing.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><u><strong>Electrical Technician</strong></u></p>\n<p>-Responsible for installation, wiring, commissioning and maintenance of electrical systems.</p>\n<p>-Inspect cables, control systems and sensors to ensure safe operation.</p>\n<p>-Troubleshoot and repair electrical faults.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><u><strong>Welder</strong></u></p>\n<p>-Responsible for welding and repair of steel structures, brackets and components.</p>\n<p>-Capable of performing common welding processes (arc welding, CO₂ welding, etc.).</p>\n<p>-Perform welding according to drawings or site requirements, ensuring weld quality meets standards.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><u><strong>Job Requirements</strong></u></p>\n<p>-Minimum 2 years of relevant working experience; experience with port machinery or heavy equipment preferred.</p>\n<p>-Able to work in outdoor conditions and at heights.</p>\n<p>-Basic English communication skills; able to understand safety instructions.</p>\n<p>-Physically fit and able to comply with safety regulations.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><u><strong>Certification Requirements</strong></u></p>\n<p>Mandatory (at least 1 of the following):</p>\n<p>-Work at Height (WAH) Certificate </p>\n<p>-Confined Space Certificate </p>\n<p>-Boom Lift Operator License </p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><u><strong>Advantageous (Preferred):</strong></u></p>\n<p>-Crane Rigger / Lifting Certificate </p>\n<p>-Forklift Operator License </p>\n<p>-WSQ Safety-related Training Certificates WSQ </p>\n<p>-Welder Qualification Certificate (for Welder position)</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><u><strong>Others</strong></u></p>\n<p>Location: PSA Singapore Terminals</p>\n<p>Working Hours: Subject to project requirements, with overtime as required</p>",
